elasticbox.title: ElasticBox CI Plug-in

elasticbox.excerpt: Provides full integration between Jenkins and ElasticBox ([http://elasticbox.com]). With this plugin, Jenkins can launch, provision, and manage Jenkins slaves on-demand in different cloud providers via ElasticBox. It also provides build steps to deploy and manage your applications, including complex, multi-tier applications that are defined as boxes in ElasticBox.

short-workspace-path.title: Short Workspace Path Plugin
short-workspace-path.name: short-workspace-path
short-workspace-path.excerpt: Use shallow directory hierarchy for build workspaces to avoid build failures on filesystems with constrained path length.

readonly-parameters.title: Readonly Parameter plugin
readonly-parameters.name: readonly-parameters
readonly-parameters.excerpt: This plugin adds support for Parameter. After the plugin is installed,in job configuration's page,you can see Readonly Parameter.

literate.title: Literate Plugin

antisamy-markup-formatter.title: OWASP Markup Formatter Plugin

dynamic-axis.title: Dynamic Axis

dynamic-axis.excerpt: This plugin allows you to define a matrix build axis that is dynamically populated from an environment variable:

teamconcert.title: Team Concert Plugin
teamconcert.name: teamconcert
teamconcert.excerpt: Integrates Jenkins with Rational Team Concert source control and build using the richer features of the build toolkit instead of the command line. With the build toolkit this plugin adds traceability links from a Jenkins build to an RTC build result, workspace and snapshot.  It also publishes links to work items, change sets and file contents captured in the snapshot.  It leverages the current RTC features and workflows that users are already familiar with such as, emails, toaster popups, reporting, dashboards, etc.

mstest.title: MSTest plugin
mstest.name: mstest
mstest.excerpt: This plugin converts MSTest TRX test reports into JUnit XML reports so it can be integrated with Jenkin's JUnit features. This plugin converts the .coveragexml files found in the project workspace to the EMMA format. You can use MSTestRunner plugin or VsTestRunner plugin to run the test and use this plugin to process the results.

build-token-root.title: Build Authorization Token Root Plugin

build-token-root.excerpt: Lets build and related REST build triggers be accessed even when anonymous users cannot see Jenkins.

reviewboard.title: Reviewboard Publisher

reviewboard.excerpt: This plugin connects to Reviewboard to create and update Review Requests. Reviewboard is a tool for conducting code reviews and this plugin will allow you to link your SCM updates, when they are pulled for a Jenkins build, to Reviewboard. Note that currently, only the Perforce SCM is supported.

pipeline-input-step.title: Pipeline: Input Step

terraform.title: Terraform Plugin

workflow-remote-loader.title: Jenkins Pipeline Remote Loader Plugin

openid4java.title: OpenID4Java API

openid4java.excerpt: This plugin provides a shared dependency on the openid4java library so that other plugins can co-operate when using this library.

sonargraph-integration.name: sonargraph-integration
sonargraph-integration.excerpt: This plugin integrates Sonargraph version 8 and newer into your build. Sonargraph allows to define an architecture for a software system and automatically checks how the code base conforms to it. For Sonargraph version 7 use Sonargraph Plugin.

bmc-rpd.title: BMC Release Package and Deployment plugin

adaptive-disconnector.title: Adaptive Disconnector Plugin

exclusive-execution.title: Jenkins Exclusive Execution Plugin

exclusive-execution.excerpt: Allows a job to be executed when no other jobs are running.

git.excerpt: This plugin allows use of Git as a build SCM, including repository browsers for several providers. A recent Git runtime is required (1.7.9 minimum, 1.8.x recommended). Interaction with the Git runtime is performed by the use of the Git Client Plugin, which is only tested on official git client. Use exotic installations at your own risk.

elOyente.excerpt: This plug-in adds job triggering based on XMPP Pub/Sub events.

systemloadaverage-monitor.title: Slave Monitor for system load average

copado.title: Copado plugin
copado.name: copado
copado.excerpt: With this plugin you can add a build step to your Jenkins project that executes a Copado Webhook API task. You would add this step after your Copado setup is finished. After the Copado Webhook is triggered, the plugin will wait for the job run to finish (or timeout). If the Job step is successful, your pipeline will continue to the next step in your pipeline; however, if it fails (or times out), the build will be marked as failed.

browser-axis-plugin.title: Browser axis

google-analytics-usage-reporter.title: Google Analytics Usage Reporter Plugin

performance.excerpt: This plugin allows you to capture reports from JMeter and JUnit . Jenkins will generate graphic charts with the trend report of performance and robustness. It includes the feature of setting the final build status as good, unstable or failed, based on the reported error percentage.
